            <p>In addition to signing up for a 4 or 5 Star Leader Assessment through a registered course provider, all candidates attending a British Canoeing 4 or 5 Star Leader Assessment are required to have preregistered with PNA using the Leadership Registration Form (LR Form). Candidates should allow three weeks to complete the preregistration process prior to the assessment. To preregister please complete the LR Form and return it to PNA, with the required fee. The LR Form will be returned to you by regular mail and must be presented to the assessor prior to your assessment. LR forms are valid for 12 months. If you are not successful, the LR Form will be returned to you, allowing you to assess again at a future date without paying another preregistration fee. <strong>Keep your LR Form in a safe place – it cannot be replaced if lost!</strong> Preregistration is required for both 4 and 5 Star Leader Assessment, and will be the start of the validation process of your qualification.</p>
