      <section id="first-aid">
        <h2>First Aid Requirements</h2>
        <p>All active coaches have a responsibility to maintain a current First Aid award, to ensure they can look after paddlers in their care. Coaches sign a declaration, upon registration for our Coaching qualifications, accepting this responsibility. Holding a valid First Aid award is also part of the British Canoeing Coach Update Scheme. Coaches who meet these requirements are recognized by PNA and British Canoeing as being active and up-to-date.</p>
        <p>In order to meet these requirements all British Canoeing Coaches (except British Canoeing / UKCC Level 1) need a recognized First Aid certificate recorded on their Paddlesports North America membership record. All First Aid training needs to be delivered by a recognized provider and include within the syllabus general First Aid and CPR (Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation). For First Aid training courses not included on our recognized list, a copy of the syllabus will need to be submitted to Paddlesports North America for approval, along with details of the course length (actual contact time) and information about the training provider.</p>
        <p>There is often confusion around 4, 6, and 8 hour courses, with many people told these courses are 'one day'. Please ensure you access an appropriate length course. <strong>We check training contact time.</strong></p>
        <p><strong>Please Note:</strong> An up-to-date First Aid and CPR certificate must be provided to PNA every three years. First Aid and CPR certifications are accepted from a number of recognized providers in North America. If any First Aid certificates have been issued outside of the United States or Canada, please contact PNA.</p>
        <p>Any coach who has a First Aid qualification recorded on their membership record, will not need to provide new evidence until their current certificate expires, and we accept that some of these existing qualifications may be less than ideal.</p>
        <p>There are no First Aid and CPR certification requirements prior to taking a UKCC Level 1 Coach training, but a minimum 1 day of training contact is highly recommended prior to coaching independently following a UKCC Level 1 Coach award.</p>
        <p>A minimum 1 day of training contact is required for UKCC Level 2 Coach training.</p>
        <p>A minimum 2 days of training contact is required for 4 Star Leader training, 5 Star Leader training, Moderate Water Endorsement, Advanced Water Endorsement, and UKCC Level 3 Coach training.</p>
        <p><strong>We do not accept First Aid or CPR certifications from online programs.</strong></p>
        <p>First Aid and CPR certification are only accepted from the following organizations:</p>
        <div class="list-group">
          <a href="http://www.redcross.org" target="_blank" class="list-group-item">American Red Cross</a>
          <a href="http://www.heart.org" target="_blank" class="list-group-item">American Heart Association</a>
